upport. At the same time, Greenberg maps the minefield of historical and structural inequalities that program facilitators must navigate to build meaningful connections with the youth they serve. Taken together, these programs shape the stories and politics of a generation and reveal how social policy can go wrong when it ignores the lives of young people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aProblem youthxCounseling ofzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aProblem youthxServices forzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aYouth and violencezCaliforniazLos Angeles. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aabiding harm.  aat risk youth.  acoming of age.  afleeting support.  aforming relationships.  ageneration.  ahistorical inequalities.  alived experiences.  alos angeles.  ameaningful connections.  apolicy revolution.  apolitics.  aprogram facilitators.  aprogramming.  aprograms.  arisk data.  aserving youth.  asocial policy.  astructural inequalities.  asupport.  aunited states.  aviolence prevention.  ayoung men and women.  ayoung people.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520969988zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www